127 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<TEXT>
<P>
After recently watching America's most popular television show, "Roseanne," I 
sincerely believe that the viewing public wants good old family programming. 
What a great half hour! I learned so much to pass on to our younger generation. 
Don't Roseanne and her Neanderthal husband set a shining example of how to act 
drunk in a bar and minutes later arrive home, as if they did not drive even the 
least bit intoxicated? Hey, and that barroom fight. There is nothing like 
punching out a vulnerable drunken man, a good lesson for the impressionable 
youth of our country. Boy, I can still feel the testosterone racing violently 
through my veins at the sound of hand meeting face. Is this how family 
programming should make me feel? 
</P>
<P>
Michael S. Hull, Playa del Rey 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
