<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTHER LOVE'S IMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In her Sept. 3 letter on "Hot Radio" (Aug. 20), Claudia Anderson criticizes KFI 
talk-show personality Mother Love and urges that Calendar instead "focus on 
someone who provides (women) with a positive image." 
</P>
<P>
In recent weeks Mother Love has called for increased tolerance and respect for 
the gay population; appealed to rap singers to tone down profanity and use 
their music to positively influence youths; urged full-figured people to have 
more self-esteem and others to respect them more. 
</P>
<P>
Could it be that Anderson has trouble transcending Mother Love's race or her 
full figure? 
</P>
<P>
ALVA MOORE-STEVENSON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
