<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITIC'S VIEW OF KFAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bernheimer's article was an unusual farewell. The first half was oh so usual 
Bernheimer -- a little wit, clever short sentences, everything intended to trap 
us into a positive response. And the second half of the critique? He owns the 
word pompous. 
</P>
<P>
It would have been classy of him to have said good-by to KFAC with a bit of 
sentiment and a kindlier attitude. I know critics must criticize, but after 
all, there is a time for more understanding of a sad situation. 
</P>
<P>
SELMA COMSKY 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Palisades 
</P>
</TEXT>
