<TEXT>
<P>
"A few people are having major cows around the city at this point. If I had 
$100,000 to $200,000 of merchandise sitting at my back door and I couldn't ship 
it, I'd have a cow. But I don't." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Bernard Lax, president of a Los Angeles clothing manufacturing firm, on the 
nervousness of apparel makers who have orders slated for stores owned by the 
