</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Congratulations to Garry Abrams on his excellent article "Amazing Disgrace." 
</P>
<P>
Who says the theater is dead? Jim Bakker has had many years of success in his 
ongoing role as a telecharlatan minister's telecharlatan minister. He is an 
experienced actor who could've given the great Olivier lessons. 
</P>
<P>
I hope Bakker's judge and jury view his apparent "psychological deterioration" 
with the eye of a skeptical theater critic. With Bakker's "sense of drama and 
staging," he just may be attempting to give the greatest performance of his 
life. 
</P>
<P>
BOB CANNING, Los Angeles 
