<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREETING GORILLAS; 
</P>
<P>
INN STILL IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's been approximately 10 years since I first saw your feature article about 
the Old Monterey Inn. In case you haven't visited 500 Martin Street lately, 
Anne and Gene Swett continue to provide the best aspects of every B&amp;B 
they've ever visited, along with their own amenities. They serve a spectacular 
full breakfast, different each morning. Throughout the day the huge Tudor house 
and gardens are open for reading, lounging or partaking of always-available hot 
and cold beverages. There are teatime cookies, followed by a sherry hour with 
memorable canapes. And the Inn's accommodations are the finest anywhere. Rates 
are from $140 to $195. Thanks for the introduction. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM B. LENZ 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente 
</P>
</TEXT>
