<P>
NAVY SAVES 32 BOAT PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By from Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SUBIC BAY NAVAL BASE, Philippines 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. Navy ship rescued 32 Vietnamese refugees from an unseaworthy craft in 
the South China Sea and brought them to this U.S.-run base 50 miles northwest 
of Manila, the Navy said Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
