<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ANTELOPE VALLEY MAN SLAIN IN ARGUMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An argument at a boardinghouse in the Lake Los Angeles area of the northern 
Antelope Valley ended in the stabbing death of a 32-year-old male tenant early 
Saturday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, whose name was withheld pending notification of relatives, was 
stabbed once in the upper chest about 3 a.m. at a boardinghouse in the 39000 
block of 182nd Street East, said Los Angeles County Sheriff's Deputy George 
Ducoulombier. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies on Saturday were searching for Robert Brian Blazer, 30, in connection 
with the killing. Authorities said Blazer, who rented a room next to the 
victim, stabbed him with an unknown object before fleeing. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was declared dead at the scene. Ducoulombier said deputies had not 
yet determined a motive for the killing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
