Virginia, 2-1 overall and 1-0 in the ACC, broke a 7-7 tie nine minutes before 
halftime on freshman Terry Kirby's three-yard run. The score came one play 
after McGonnigal completed a 61-yard pass play. 
</P>
<P>
McGonnigal, who had six catches for 157 yards, carried his 42-yard reception to 
the Yellow Jacket 19, setting up a 30-yard field goal by Jake McInerney late in 
the third quarter. 
</P>
