<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNIDENTIFIED BODY FOUND IN HOUSE FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Firefighters, responding to a house fire Thursday night in East San Diego, 
discovered a man's badly burned body in a rear bedroom, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified man was 6 feet tall and weighed 171 pounds, said Cal Vine, 
deputy coroner. 
</P>
<P>
It took 22 firefighters more than four hours to contain the blaze at 7739 
Shorewood Drive, which began at 9:54 p.m. Thursday, fire Capt. Allan Macdonald 
said. An investigation revealed that the fire had been deliberately set by 
someone who spread flammable liquid throughout the house and ignited it, said 
Detective John Buono of the Metro Arson Strike Team. Homicide detectives are 
investigating. 
</P>
<P>
Damage to the single-story, wood house was estimated at $50,000, Macdonald 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
