NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 1,000 New York Giants' season tickets have disappeared, but team 
officials say they won't know whether they were lost or stolen until the Giants 
home opener today. 
</P>
<P>
A truck delivering a box of tickets to the Meadowlands three weeks ago had made 
several stops on the way, and officials say the box might have fallen from the 
truck. 
</P>
<P>
The tickets, for seats throughout Giants Stadium, had already been purchased by 
season-ticket holders, team spokesman Ed Croke said. New color-coded tickets 
have been printed and sent to the ticket holders, he said. 
</P>
