<HEADLINE>
<P>
HANAUER SETS TWO SPEED RECORDS IN GOLD CUP TRIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chip Hanauer, who will go for his eighth consecutive APBA Gold Cup victory 
today, broke the unlimited hydroplane records for one-and two-lap qualifying 
runs Saturday on the 2.5-mile Mission Bay course. 
</P>
<P>
Hanauer, of Seattle, piloted his Circus Circus turbine-powered boat to the 
fastest unlimited lap ever, 158.870 m.p.h. That bettered the record of 156.169 
set here last year by Tom D'Eath in the Miss Budweiser. 
</P>
<P>
Hanauer's two-lap qualifying mark of 158.297 m.p.h. broke his old record of 
149.031 set here in 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
