Public hearings continue Monday on the environmental impact report for the 
controversial Foothill/Trabuco Specific Plan, which would establish development 
guidelines for 6,500 acres of backcountry east of Mission Viejo. County 
planners have recommended that 1,700 new homes be allowed in the hill and 
canyon country. 
</P>
