<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROHRABACHER AND FUNDING FOR THE ARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am sorry that Rep. Dana Rohrabacher feels that art is "frivolous" and that 
he, in all his wisdom, feels compelled to stand in judgment of one's creative 
expression. Our country was founded by visionaries, willing to take chances. 
</P>
<P>
After generations of personal repression, our founding fathers (and mothers) 
were willing to give their lives for the opportunity of enjoying the basic 
freedom of self-expression. 
</P>
<P>
How sad that now our leaders in Congress attack that right as frivolous. Stay 
in line. Don't make waves. Our country must continue to progress without 
basking in the laurels of its past. 
</P>
<P>
The future is a product of the creative spirit embodied in our artists, our 
designers, our teachers and all those with a vision of what could be. 
Rohrabacher and Sen. Jesse Helms seem threatened by the power of this creative 
spirit and have a wish to bask in all that is comfortable and accountable. 
</P>
<P>
Our culture will stagnate without persons in power with vision, imagination and 
creativity! Art is not frivolous. It is the spirit we need as a people to 
continue and be great. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD ALAN HALES 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 
</P>
