GRAND OPENINGS; 
</P>
<P>
3 PACIFIC RIDGE COMMUNITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lyon Communities Inc. will be previewing model homes in three sections of 
single-family homes at Pacific Ridge, a new neighborhood in the hills of Aliso 
Viejo in south Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
The Breeze homes, designed especially for young families, are two-storied and 
have 3 and 4 bedrooms and 2 1/2 baths. Prices range from $269,990 to $299,990. 
</P>
<P>
Homes in The Crest area are targeted to growing families and/or move-up 
families and are two-storied residences with 3 and 4 bedrooms, optional bonus 
rooms and attached 3-car garages. Prices range from 283,990 to $319,990. 
</P>
<P>
The Highlands will represent Pacific Ridge's largest homes and are designed for 
established and/or move-up buyers. They have 3 to 5 bedrooms, up to 3 full 
baths and 3-car garages. Prices range from $309,990 to $349,990. 
</P>
<P>
Sales begin this weekend, with model homes open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. in all 
three Pacific Ridge areas, reached from the Alicia Parkway exit of the Santa 
Ana (5) Freeway, then right on Moulton Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Paula Homes 
</P>
<P>
Las Pasadas, a development of single-family homes with a Spanish Revival 
architectural theme, at 157 Beckwith Road in west Santa Paula, is staging a 
grand opening today with three decorated models. 
</P>
<P>
Three floor plans with 3 or 4 bedrooms are available in one- and two-story 
designs ranging in size from 1,438 to 2,019 square feet. A total of 86 homes 
will eventually complete the walled community, according to the developer, Mesa 
Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
All homes will include front-yard landscaping with stuccoed-block side and rear 
yard walls for privacy. A $90 homeowners' monthly maintenance fee will be added 
to the purchase price ranging from $275,000 to $288,000. 
</P>
<P>
Sales office is open from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m., except Tuesdays and Wednesdays. 
</P>
