<P>
</P>
<P>
Number of active U.S. pilots: 694,016. Non-commercial pilot license holders 
total about 300,000, of which about 12,000 reside in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
Number of aircraft: 222,000, all but 4,500 of which are general aviation. 
</P>
<P>
Note: General aviation includes all aircraft that are not commercial air 
carriers. Van Nuys is almost solely a general aviation facility -- the largest 
in the nation. John Wayne Airport is the fifth busiest air facility in the 
U.S., just ahead of Denver's Stapleton Airport. Chicago's O'Hare is the 
busiest, followed by Atlanta, Dallas-Ft. Worth and Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Sources: Federal Aviation Administration, Aircraft Owners &amp; Pilots Assn. 
</P>
