</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More Cleaning -- Volunteers helped clean the Upper Newport Bay and Bolsa Chica 
ecological reserves of trash Saturday. This week the cleanups continue at eight 
Orange County beaches, part of a statewide effort organized by the California 
Coastal Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Volunteer groups and individuals will gather beginning at 8 a.m. Saturday at 
the following beaches to help clean up trash left by summer crowds: Crystal 
Cove, Bolsa Chica, Huntington and Trestles state beaches, Huntington City 
Beach, and Main Beach and Heisler Park in Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
