<HEADLINE>
<P>
REDEMPTION RATE FOR RECYCLED CANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I agree with your editorial ("Definitely Worth a Toast!" Sept. 4) that 
consumers deserve "more than a fistful of pennies for their effort" in 
returning soda bottles and empty beer cans, and that the state "should approve 
the nickel reward." But I would suggest an additional piece of legislation 
which immediately upon enactment would eliminate most bottles and cans from our 
parks and roads. Simply stated, require a like number of empty containers to be 
returned at each purchase of full containers. 
</P>
<P>
Thirsty Californians who aren't attracted to returning empties for a redemption 
fee -- no matter how big it gets -- will tote those bottles and cans to make a 
new purchase to quench their thirst. 
</P>
<P>
RON BARTH 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Palos Verdes 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
